hopobject.body: Thanks for calling philhealth.winsite.com The SEC's civil fraud charges concern the role of a large hedge fund, Paulson & Co. Inc., and its billionaire president, John A. Paulson, in helping to choose the assets that would decide the value of the investment. While Paulson played a significant role in selecting the assets, the company also shorted over $1 billion of those assets through credit default swaps, the SEC said.
